Mohammad Ali Akhtar was on second shift at Premier Stores in Manchester .
He was only on his second shift when the man stormed in brandishing a large kitchen knife and demanded all the money from the till .
The robber, wearing dark coloured clothing, leapt over the counter and attacked him .
Mr Akhtar said: 'In those few seconds of my life I thought, "well I've just got to tackle him", then I felt the sharp stabs to my ear, nose and finger'